{
  "texts": [
    "We evaluate the model using the retro-synthesis prediction task from USPTO-50k and BioChem (Zheng et al., 2022), wherein the model is tasked with predicting the corresponding reactants and catalysts given the products.",
    "We evaluate the model performance from two aspects: 1.",
    "Coverage, which indicates how much of the true products are covered by the model outputs, reflecting the accuracy of the reaction predictions.",
    "Due to the inability of LLMs to guarantee that the predicted SMILES codes are entirely consistent with the ground truth, there might be cases where different SMILES codes are predicted for the same molecule.",
    "Therefore, we do not opt for the traditional Exact Match metric."
  ]
}